# Test during development

Run the **smallest test scope that can catch your regression** after substantive edits ‚Äî not only at task end. Full gate remains [static-analysis.mdc](static-analysis.mdc) (`mvn verify` once before marking done).

## Tiered ladder

| When | Command |
|------|---------|
| After compile-only / trivial edit | Skip tests until next substantive change |
| After editing one module | See **module commands** below |
| After editing public API or SPI | Module tests + downstream module if listed in **impact map** |
| Before marking task done | `mvn verify` (once) |

### Module commands

```bash
# Unit + embedded-server tests (no Docker)
mvn -Pfast -pl commons test
mvn -Pfast -pl client test
mvn -Pfast -pl server test
mvn -Pfast -pl bridge/stomp4j-kafka-bridge test

# Full module tests (Docker required for @Tag("integration"))
mvn -pl client test
mvn -pl server test
mvn -pl bridge/stomp4j-kafka-bridge test
mvn -pl spring test
mvn -pl quarkus test

# Single failing or new test (fastest feedback)
mvn -pl <module> test -Dtest=ClassName#methodName
```

Use `-Pfast` while iterating on logic that has unit/embedded coverage. Run **without** `-Pfast` when you touch transport, protocol, session, broker integration, or anything tagged `@Tag("integration")`.

## Change impact map

| You changed | Run before continuing |
|-------------|------------------------|
| `commons` / `commons.protocol` | `mvn -pl commons test` then `mvn -Pfast -pl client,server test`; if framing/commands changed ‚Üí `mvn -pl client,server test` (Docker) |
| `client` transport or protocol | `mvn -pl client test` (Docker) |
| `client` public API only | `mvn -Pfast -pl client test`; add `mvn -pl client test` if behaviour is async/broker-facing |
| `server.session` / channels / handlers | `mvn -pl server test` |
| `server` public API | `mvn -Pfast -pl server test` |
| `bridge/` | `mvn -pl bridge/stomp4j-kafka-bridge test` |
| `spring/` or `quarkus/` | Respective module tests after core modules green |
| Test infra (`*.tests.infra`, `broker.xml`) | All modules that use that infra ‚Äî at minimum `mvn -pl client test` |

## Production-code checklist

When editing **production** code (not only test files), apply patterns from [stomp4j-tests.mdc](stomp4j-tests.mdc):

- Protocol/transport/session change ‚Üí run integration tests for that module.
- After SUBSCRIBE in new broker tests ‚Üí `StompTestSupport.settleSubscription()` before SEND.
- WebSocket broker URL ‚Üí port **61614** (`webSocketUrl()`), not OpenWire **61616**.
- Broker-backed tests ‚Üí `@Execution(SAME_THREAD)`, `@ExtendWith(StompContainer.class)` when possible.
- Awaitility ‚Üí always set `atMost`; ensure `atMost` > any `pollDelay`.

## When a test fails

1. **While fixing:** re-run single test or module test only ‚Äî see [stomp4j-test-failure-diagnosis.mdc](stomp4j-test-failure-diagnosis.mdc) ¬ß1‚Äì¬ß4.
2. **After green:** one report file per root cause or session; full `mvn verify` once.

Do **not** loop full `mvn verify` after every incremental fix.

